# OpenClaw_Harsh - Personal AI Assistant

Personal OpenClaw (formerly Clawd/Moltbot) deployment on DigitalOcean VPS with WhatsApp integration.
Self-hosted AI personal assistant powered by Anthropic Claude, running on a $6/mo DigitalOcean droplet.

## Owner
- **Name:** Harsh Sharma
- **Purpose:** Personal life assistant via WhatsApp
- **Hosting:** DigitalOcean VPS (Ubuntu 24.04)
- **LLM:** Personal Anthropic API key (Claude Opus 4.6)
- **GitHub:** https://github.com/Harsharma2308/OpenClaw_Harsh

## Tech Stack
- **Runtime:** Node.js 22
- **Agent:** OpenClaw (MIT licensed, github.com/openclaw/openclaw)
- **LLM Provider:** Anthropic Claude API (personal key, pay-per-token)
- **Messaging:** WhatsApp bridge (built-in, QR code pairing)
- **Deployment:** Docker Compose on DigitalOcean droplet
- **Security:** Loopback-only gateway, SSH tunnel for dashboard, UFW firewall

## Project Structure
```
OpenClaw_Harsh/
├── .cursorrules           # Project rules (this file)
├── CLAUDE.md              # Symlink → .cursorrules
├── .gitignore             # Exclude secrets, .env, credentials
├── setup/
│   ├── README.md          # Setup instructions & cost breakdown
│   ├── droplet-setup.sh   # VPS bootstrap (user, node, swap, firewall)
│   ├── openclaw-config.json5  # OpenClaw config template
│   ├── soul.md            # Personality / SOUL.md for the assistant
│   └── deploy.sh          # One-command deploy to VPS
└── .claude/
    └── settings.local.json
```

## Key Commands
- **Deploy to VPS:** `./setup/deploy.sh <DROPLET_IP>`
- **SSH into VPS:** `ssh openclaw@<DROPLET_IP>`
- **Dashboard (via tunnel):** `ssh -L 18789:127.0.0.1:18789 openclaw@<DROPLET_IP>` then open http://localhost:18789
- **Check status:** `ssh openclaw@<DROPLET_IP> 'openclaw gateway status'`
- **View logs:** `ssh openclaw@<DROPLET_IP> 'journalctl --user-unit openclaw-gateway -f'`
- **Backup:** `ssh openclaw@<DROPLET_IP> 'tar -czf ~/backup-$(date +%Y%m%d).tar.gz ~/.openclaw/'`

## VPS Details
- **Provider:** DigitalOcean ($200 credit / 60-day trial, then $6/mo)
- **Spec:** 2 vCPU, 1GB RAM + 1GB swap, Ubuntu 24.04
- **Region:** SFO3 or nearest
- **Firewall:** SSH (22) only, gateway on loopback (127.0.0.1:18789)

## Cost Breakdown
- **VPS:** $6/mo (free for first 60 days with trial credit)
- **Anthropic API:** ~$1-2/hr when actively chatting (pay-per-token)
- **Heartbeat cost:** ~48 LLM turns/day at 30min intervals during active hours

## Security Rules
- NEVER commit API keys, .env files, or credentials to git
- Gateway MUST bind to loopback only (never expose port 18789)
- Access dashboard only via SSH tunnel
- WhatsApp dmPolicy set to "pairing" (explicit approval required)
- Docker sandbox enabled for non-main agent sessions
- Run `openclaw doctor` regularly for security audit

## Architecture
```
[WhatsApp on Phone] → [WhatsApp Bridge]
                           ↓
                    [OpenClaw Gateway]  ← SSH tunnel → [Dashboard UI]
                           ↓
                    [Agent Session]
                           ↓
                    [Anthropic Claude API]
```
- Gateway is the single long-running process (Node.js, systemd managed)
- Agent loads SOUL.md + workspace context on each session
- Heartbeat fires every 30min during active hours (08:00-22:00 PT)
- WhatsApp bridge handles QR auth, message routing, media

## Personality (SOUL.md)
The assistant personality is defined in `setup/soul.md` and deployed to `~/.openclaw/workspace/SOUL.md` on the VPS.
Edit locally, redeploy with `./setup/deploy.sh`.

## iMessage (Future)
Requires a Mac running BlueBubbles server. Skipped for initial setup.
Can be added later with a Mac Mini or Mac-in-cloud service.

## Important Notes
- This is a PERSONAL project - no NVIDIA infrastructure, keys, or proxy
- Anthropic API key is personal and paid out of pocket
- Keep workspace files (SOUL.md, USER.md) private - they contain personal context
- OpenClaw updates: `openclaw update --channel stable`
- WhatsApp session may need re-linking periodically (check logs)
